<dl id="n01118j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n01" href="#n01118j">N01 (VI.B.10)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n01all.htm#n01118j"> 118(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> obi = stomacher <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n01118j"><li>FW 64.02 </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/lexc.htm#n01118j">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/l39c.htm#n01118j">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n01118j">MS BL 47472-153</ms> </li><li>JJA 45:193 <a name="c3d" href="../../FF/fdra/cda.htm#c3d">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/c/c3d.htm#n01118j">Draft: I.3&sect;1.3</a>/2.3/3.3</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[GLIMPSES AT JAPAN]</font> It is extremely difficult for the foreigner to penetrate into the real home-life of a Japanese <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> Our host advances and greets us with a low obeisance <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> We are now introduced to his &ldquo;disgraceful and abominable old woman&rdquo; (wife) <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> The ladies are also wearing the <mark><i>obi</i>, a belt a foot wide</mark>, which is wound round the body over the <i>kimono</i>. <small> <a name="IT27jan23" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#IT27jan23"><cite title="source">Irish Times</cite></a> (27 January 1923) 10/2</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
